{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reverse the cuts made to police services across the UK since 2010 to save lives!",
        "additional_details": "The latest statistics show a 14% year-on-year increase in criminal offences recorded by forces across England and Wales. \r\n\r\nKnife crime has gone up by 21%.\r\n \r\nGun crime has risen by 20%.\r\n\r\nDomestic burglary has risen by 32%.\r\n\r\nVehicle-related crimes have increased by 18%.\r\n\r\nThe murder and manslaughter rate in England and Wales has risen to the highest in a decade.\r\n\r\nWhen will the PM and Home Secretary act? They have Special Branch protection so they'll never be victims of crimes. What about us?!",
        "background": "We call on the government to reverse cuts made to all UK police services since 2010, give our police officers a proper pay rise, and save our officers' pensions! This has gone on for too long and we want the government to support, equip, and fund our police properly so they can protect us properly!",
